==Overview==
This is a translation of the [[:de:Vorlage:Imagemap]] from the german Wikipedia. It is more powerful than the normal Imagemap-Template.  ImageMap for linking image to other address rather than to its own image description page only.

== Format ==

<pre><nowiki>{{Imagemap
 | image= 
 | width= 
 | link= 
 | Alt= 
 | tooltip= 
 | form= 
 | desc= 
}}
</nowiki></pre>

oder
<pre><nowiki>
{{Imagemap | image | link | Alternativtext | width}}
</nowiki></pre>

== Parameters ==

=== Long ===

Parameters which are duty are written in '''big''' letters.

{| class="prettytable"
|-
 | '''image'''
 | The image, which should be shown. Without ''File:''.
|- class="hintergrundfarbe2"
 | ''width''
 | The [[Wikipedia:Picture tutorial#Resizing|width]] which should be used (also possible: ''frameless'' und ''upright'').
|-
 | ''link''
 | The [[Lemma (linguistics)|Lemma]] or the page, which should be [[Hyperlink|linked]] . If empty, the description of the picture will be used. If [[Form (Geometry)|form]] (see later) is used, no link will be used.

The link also can be weblink, if he starts with ''http://'', ''https://'', ''ftp://'' oder ''ftps://''.
|- class="hintergrundfarbe2"
 | ''Alt''
 | Alternativtext which should bei used. [http://de.selfhtml.org/html/grafiken/einbinden.htm#referenz Alternativtext]. If empty, ''tooltip'' or ''link'' will be used. This one should be used anyway!
|-
 | ''tooltip''
 | ''[[tooltip]]''-text which is shown, when the cursor is a certain time on the picture. If empty, ''link'' will be used.
|- class="hintergrundfarbe2"
 | ''form''
 | [[Form (Geometry)|form]] like in [[mw:Extension:ImageMap#Syntax_description|MediaWiki Extension ImageMap, section „Syntax description“]] explained ''(poly, rect'' und ''circle)''. See also: [[meta:User:Dapete/ImageMapEdit#English|ImageMapEdit]].
|-
 | ''desc''
 | Where should the logo that links to the description page of the picture be placed? Possible data: ''top-left'', ''top-right'', ''bottom-left'', ''bottom-right'', ''none''. If nothing is given ''bottom-left'' will be used.
|- class="hintergrundfarbe2"
 | ''inline''
 | Please write ''x'' , if the image will be placed in continuous text.
|}

=== Short ===

In the short form just write: <tt class="hintergrundfarbe2"><nowiki>{{Imagemap|image|link|Alternativtext|width}}</nowiki></tt> Only the first paramter is needed, but it is better to use the first three anyway.

